notesStmt.note: Persian customs stamps solar dated 1312 (1933 CE) (f. [0]r, 182v); note in black ink f. 182v.

msContents.summary: Commentary on the Zīj-i jadīd-i Sulṭānī which comprises tables of calendar calculations, trigonometry, planets, and stars. Space has been left for some missing diagrams and others have been tipped in.

author.persName: Birjandī, ʻAbd al-ʻAlī ibn Muḥammad ibn Ḥusayn, active 16th century
برجندى، عبد العلى بن محمد بن حسين،

supportDesc.extent: 183 leaves : 230 x 180 (180 x 115) mm, bound to 240 x 185 mm

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in nastaʻlīq in black ink, pointed.

decoDesc.decoNote: Diagrams in red; overlining and rubrications in red.
Notations and partial stamp on insert

binding.p: Brown leather over pasteboard (Type III) with blind stamped central mandorla with two pendants on the vertical axis and three narrow frame rules; plain paper doublure.

origin.p: Copy completed in Rabīʻ al-Thānī 1097 AH (1686 CE) (f. 182r).

history.provenance: Formerly owned by David Eugene Smith (signature in pencil, f. 182v).
